                    <div class="typeofhazard">Safety gear</div>
                    <div class="howtoavoid">When working on the site, always wear a hard hat and safety shoes.
                        When climbing up the tower, always wear the safety harness.</div>
                </div></td></tr></table></div>

                </li>

            </ol>

        </div>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Shut down the IT-equipment for the whole sensor site.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Open the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Suppression System Control Panel</span></em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Ensure, that indication lamps and push button are correctly identified on the
                    control panel.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Use a multimeter to verify, that the control panel batteries are properly
                    charged.</span>
                <div class="itemgroup info">System voltage is 12V DC with a +/- 0.5V tolerance.</div>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch off the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Suppression System Circuit Breaker</span></em> at the
                            <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Main Distribution Board (MDB)</span></em> and verify
                    that the removal of the AC power automatically switches the control panel to the
                        <em class="ph i">Backup Battery System</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Ensure, that the removal of AC power initiates a visual and audible trouble
                    signal.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch on the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Suppression System Circuit Breaker</span></em> at the
                        <em class="ph i">MDB</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Ensure, that the fault indicators are off.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch off the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Suppression System</span></em> at the
                    control panel by turning the key on the main switch (see item 3 in <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Fire_Suppression_System_Control_Panel">Figure 1</a>).</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Fire_Suppression_System_Control_Panel"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 1. </span>Fire Suppression System Control Panel</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-XX-X-XXX-A-D2714-06520-A-A-1.png" />
                        <dl class="dl">
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">1</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Terminal Blocks</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">2</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Screws</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">3</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Main Switch</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">4</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Battery 12V/7Ah (fire
            suppression system)</span></dd>

                            
                        </dl>

                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Unscrew and remove the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Manual Actuator</span></em> and the
                            <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Electrical Actuator</span></em> assembly (see item
                    1 and 2 in <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Actuator">Figure 2</a>)
                    by turning the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Knurled Nut</span></em> (see item 6 in <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Actuator">Figure 2</a>)
                    counter clockwise.</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone sidelegend" id="fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Actuator"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 2. </span>HFC-227 Cylinder release actuator</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-XX-X-XXX-A-D2714-06517-A-A-1.png" height="676" width="629" />
                        <dl class="dl">
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">1</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Manual Actuator</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">2</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Electrical Actuator</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">3</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Pressure Sensor</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">4</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Safety Pin</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">5</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Discharge Pipe Nut</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">6</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Knurled Nut</span></dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">7</dt>

                                <dd class="dd"><span class="ph">Pressure Gauge</span></dd>

                            
                        </dl>

                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Remove the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Smoke/Heat Detector</span></em> from the base by rotating the detector
                    head counter-clockwise and removing the detector head.</span>
                <div class="itemgroup stepresult">Ensure, that the removal of a detector from the circuit initiates a
                    visual and audible alarm.</div>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Reinstall the removed detector by rotating the detector head clockwise.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Activate the manual call point (see <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__call_point_manual">Figure 3</a>) and verify an alarm signal.</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__call_point_manual"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 3. </span>Call point (manual)</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/Call_point_manual.png" height="279" width="563" />
                        <dl class="dl">
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">1</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Call point - ready</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">2</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Call point - activated</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">3</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Call point - reset fork</dd>

                            
                        </dl>

                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Deactivate the manual call point with the reset fork (see item 3 in <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__call_point_manual">Figure 3</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd"><strong class="ph b">Ensure, that the auxiliary relay output signal operates correctly:</strong></span>
                <ol type="a" class="ol substeps">
                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Apply the artificial smoke on the smoke detector.</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup stepresult">The detector will activate and the bell will ring (<strong class="ph b">1st stage
                                alarm</strong>).</div>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Use the heat gun to activate the heat detector.</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup stepresult">The detector will activate the sounder and the red flasher
                                (<strong class="ph b">2nd stage alarm</strong>).</div>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">If <strong class="ph b">thirty seconds later</strong> both detectors are still in active mode,
                            the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">FM-200 gas</span></em> will be
                            released:</span>
                        
                            <ol class="ol" type="i">
                                <li class="li">Check, if the gas has been released at the removed
                                    actuator.</li>

                                <li class="li">Check, if the safety pin is pressed out.</li>

                                <li class="li">Check, if the amber light is activated.</li>

                            </ol>

                        
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Verify, that signals to BATB (<em class="ph i">Fire Alarm</em>, <em class="ph i">Fire Alarm
                                Fault</em> and <em class="ph i">FM Release</em>) are operational.</span>
                        
                            <ol class="ol" type="i">
                                <li class="li">A <em class="ph i">Fire Alarm</em> should enlighten the "Fire" LED (see <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Fire_Suppression_System_Control_Panel">Figure 1</a>).</li>

                                <li class="li">A "Fire Alarm Fault" should be indicated by the flashing amber
                                    light and the audible signal.</li>

                                <li class="li">An <em class="ph i">FM Release</em> should enlighten the red LED named
                                    “Extinguishant Released”.</li>

                            </ol>

                        
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Verify, that the exterior warning lights are operating.</span>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Verify, that the <em class="ph i">HVAC</em>, <em class="ph i">MAIN MDB</em> and <em class="ph i">UPS DB</em> units
                            shutdown upon fire alarm.</span>
                    </li>

                </ol>

            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Reinstall the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Manual Actuator</span></em> and the
                    <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Electrical Actuator</span></em> (see item 1 and 2 in
                        <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Actuator">Figure 2</a>)
                    by turning the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Knurled Nut</span></em> (see item 6 in <a class="xref" href="#fire_detection_and_suppression_system___functional_check__Actuator">Figure 2</a>)
                    clockwise.</span>
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

